# ask_basic.algo.ct
# Relation: Ask(probe, history, mark, evidence) in the concrete parity fixture.
#
# Scope:
#   Bounded algorithm-form witness for the Ask representative quadruples and
#   the bounded fixture sweep in tests/test_ask.c. The semantic relation is:
#
#     mark = evidence = (probe + depth(history)) mod 2.
#
# Program:
#   Production i emits 1 followed by the six-bit binary index i. During the
#   first input-length steps, every head bit equal to 1 appends the certificate
#   for that input position. Head bit 0 appends nothing. The test harness runs
#   exactly input_length steps and compares the remaining tape with the
#   expected positional certificate for that Ask input.
#
# Boundary:
#   This is a bounded trace witness, not an unbounded cyclic-tag decider for
#   Ask. See docs/ask_algo_design.md for the full recognizer contract and the
#   obstruction.
PRODUCTIONS 64
1000000
1000001
1000010
1000011
1000100
1000101
1000110
1000111
1001000
1001001
1001010
1001011
1001100
1001101
1001110
1001111
